sfserver - Simple File Server
--------------------------------
Examples using wget (no SSL):
- put file on server:
	wget -O - --post-file=/etc/passwd http://<server>:<port>/etc.passwd
	wget -O - --post-data `base64 -w 0 /etc/passwd` \
		http://<server>:<port>/b/etc.passwd
	(base64 is part of coreutils on Linux, but on FreeBSD is the package
		that may be not installed by default especially on webservers)
- get file from server:
	wget http://<server>:<port>/wso23 -O wso23.php

For using with SSL add --no-check-certificate option to wget command
For using with SSL and clients certificate, use wget options (see below):
  --no-check-certificate
  --certificate <client_certificate_file>
  --private-key <client_private_key>

SSL support
--------------
(based on article http://www.opennet.ru/base/sec/ssl_cert.txt.html)

Generate server self-signed certificate and private key (without passphrase):
- openssl req -new -newkey rsa:2048 -nodes -keyout ca.key -x509 -days 365 \
	-subj /C=RU/ST=Msk/L=Msk/emailAddress=warcraft.stranger@gmail.ru \
	-out ca.crt

Generate client private key and Client Certificate Request (CSR):
- openssl req -new -newkey rsa:2048 -nodes -keyout client01.key \
	-subj /C=RU/ST=Msk/L=Msk/CN=Client1/emailAddress=warcraft.stranger@yandex.ru \
	-out client01.csr

Sign CSR with CA (see <ca.config> as example):
- openssl ca -config ca.config -in client01.csr -out client01.crt -batch

Documentation
-------------------
Documentation generated by gendoc.sh script. Epydoc package need to be
installed.
